To capture interactions within a system, an alternative is to use mutual information between parts of a system. We can measure this via joint entropy, which extends the Shannon-Wiener index by considering interactions (Szabo et al. 2014; Varley and Hoel 2022). For a collection of n entities, the (pairwise) joint entropy is given byHjoint=-∑i=0n∑j=0np(i,j)log(p(i,j)),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
